---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Hot Water Endeavour Hills | Gas, Heat-Pump, Solar, Same-Day Repairs | (03) 9003 0108"
  description="Hot water specialists in Endeavour Hills — same-day repairs, gas / heat-pump / solar / electric replacements. Endeavour Hills 3802, established 1980s-90s estates. Solar Vic rebate. VBA-licensed plumbers and gasfitters."
  canonical="https://sehotwater.com.au/endeavour-hills/">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Endeavour Hills 3802 &middot; Established hillside estates</span>
      <h1>Hot water in <span class="accent">Endeavour Hills</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        Endeavour Hills is a mature 1980s-90s subdivision tucked into the lower
        Dandenong Ranges foothills. Steep blocks, established gardens, mostly
        owner-occupier, gas storage units now 25&ndash;30 years old hitting
        end-of-life. Same-day repairs, full replacements, and the $1,000 Solar
        Vic rebate handled in-house.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Why Endeavour Hills</span>
      <h2>The Endeavour Hills hot water story.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>1980s-90s housing on sloping blocks &mdash; mostly external storage tanks.</h3>
        <p>
          Endeavour Hills was a major Greater Dandenong release through the
          1980s and into the early 1990s. The blocks slope toward the foothills,
          the houses are split-level or double-storey on the slope, and the
          original gas storage tanks (Rheem Stellar 170/250, Vulcan 250L) are
          mounted on a concrete pad on the lower side of the block. We see a lot
          of 25&ndash;30+ year old units still struggling on. The cylinder
          life is well exceeded; the anode is long-gone. We replace
          3&ndash;4 a week here.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Owner-occupier majority &mdash; ideal for the rebate.</h3>
        <p>
          Endeavour Hills is heavily owner-occupier (~70%), settled families,
          mostly under the $210K household income cap. That makes the suburb
          an excellent fit for the Solar Vic heat-pump rebate: a 280&ndash;315L
          heat-pump (Reclaim, Sanden, Stiebel) lands at $3K&ndash;$4.5K net.
          Running cost savings are particularly strong here because the
          existing 25-year-old gas storage units are inefficient even
          compared to a modern gas instantaneous.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Sloping blocks &mdash; compressor placement requires planning.</h3>
        <p>
          Heat-pump compressors need a level concrete pad with clearances for
          airflow (typically 500mm front, 200mm sides). On Endeavour Hills
          sloping blocks we sometimes need a small concrete pad poured before
          the compressor goes down &mdash; we include that in the quote.
          Acoustic placement is also planned: we keep compressors well clear
          of neighbour bedrooms and your own bedroom windows.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">Typical Endeavour Hills jobs.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>25-30 year old Rheem Stellar 170L gas storage &mdash; like-for-like Rinnai HotFlo 170L ($1.9K&ndash;$2.4K)</li>
          <li>Gas storage to heat-pump conversion (Sanden 315L split-system, compressor on slope-aware pad) &mdash; $4K&ndash;$4.5K net after rebates</li>
          <li>Solar hot water full install &mdash; north-facing roof orientation excellent here; $5K&ndash;$7K net</li>
          <li>Tempering valve retrofit (mandatory under AS 3500 at 50&deg;C max for new installs) &mdash; $300&ndash;$450</li>
          <li>Same-day no-hot-water repair &mdash; $200&ndash;$500</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <h2>Other South East service areas.</h2>
      <div class="areas-grid">
        <a class="area-pill" href="/berwick/">Berwick</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/cranbourne/">Cranbourne</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/narre-warren/">Narre Warren</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/hampton-park/">Hampton Park</a>
        <a class="area-pill" href="/south-east-melbourne/">All South East Melbourne</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free Endeavour Hills hot water quote.</h2>
        <p>Old tank ready to retire? Quote within 24 hours.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn btn-primary" href="tel:+61390030108">&#9742; Call (03) 9003 0108</a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Book online</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
